ecm_front_end_common: drop the ctl_table sentinel

Since kernel 6.11 sysctl tables are sized with ARRAY_SIZE and an empty
terminating entry fails the registration check ("sysctl table check
failed: net/ecm/(null) procname is null"), so the whole net/ecm table
- front_end_conn_limit, udp/tcp_denied_ports, unidir_accel_*,
udp_ipsec_port - silently failed to register. This is the only
sentinel left in code this package compiles.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

--- a/frontends/ecm_front_end_common.c
+++ b/frontends/ecm_front_end_common.c
@@ -1436,7 +1436,6 @@ static struct ctl_table ecm_front_end_sy
 		.proc_handler	= &ecm_front_end_esp_spi_passthrough_enable_handler,
 	},
 #endif
-	{}
 };
 
